  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (INT-5 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package carries W-EP-01 (Critical: a bindsClaim IRI with no prov:wasDerivedFrom) and W-AL-02 (Medium: hasUncertaintyQuantification declared true but no hasSensitivityAnalysis present). The combination is Critical+Medium, which falls below the Critical+High threshold required for COMPOUND-01 to fire.",
